						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">GradualGames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I keep hearing this from folks. Really? 15$? That's going to break the bank?<br /></div><br /><br />$15 is dirst cheap if it's something you know you want.  But it's going to deter me from just playing with it to see if it's cool or not.  There's a bunch of cool free &quot;learn to code&quot; platforms, seeing that I have to pay for this one made me shrug and move on to another. <br /><br />$15 is also (depending on your family dynamics) not cheap if you're a 10 year old without much money of your own, which would deter them from just downloading it and playing with it.<br /><br />So no, it's not going to break the bank. But it's (unfortunately) a hurdle that keeps people from trying it out.  Some sort of trial/shareware model might help them a lot.  Get people to realize it's cool first.  After that, $15 is cheap.</div>

					
